    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p><a href="https://drupal.org/project/domain_rules" target="_blank">Domain rules</a> is a module I (hardly) maintain, but do it with fun.<br />
I was a part of a project long time ago (<a href="http://www.index.org.il/" target="_blank">http://www.index.org.il/</a>) which used <a href="https://drupal.org/project/domain" target="_blank">Domain Access</a> as a main feature, and as a fan of <a href="https://drupal.org/project/rules" blank="">Rules</a> I jumped into developing few events and actions to integrate between them.<br />
While I didn't encoutner any need for Domain Access for long time, the fact that developers uses Domain Rules and sometimes ask for new features, gives me a great pleasure.</p>
<p>So, except some bug fixing in the new version, I added two new actions:</p>
<ul><li>domain_rules_action_variable_set - set variables such as site name, site email, and more.</li>
<li>domain_rules_action_add_domain_alias - add alias to a domain</li>
</ul><p>Hope those new features actually come to use, and that I didn't harm anything with existing features.<br />
Good luck,<br />
Shushu</p>
